    public class DataValueDouble
extends AbstractModifiableDataValue<Double>
    Data series storing double-precision floating-point numbers (represented as primitive double for efficiency).

    O. J. Coleman

        public void setValue(Double value)
        Description copied from interface: DataValue

      • getEmptyValue

        public Double getEmptyValue()
        Description copied from interface: DataValue
        Get the value corresponding to an empty value. For floating-point numbers this is either Double.NaN or Float.NaN. For integer types it is Long.MIN_VALUE, Integer.MIN_VALUE, etc. For all other types this is usually null.
        Specified by:
        getEmptyValue in interface DataValue<Double>
